<subSubSection id="203E0292CDDC21D13FC703CA6F05760E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E66DE6DECBB8FD539371A9B245523F43" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F97EFC7F3650CB12E2B9AAF77C5E4BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.9 mm long (n = 1); 2.23
<normalizedToken id="57294128A00721EE8831FDED4F2BDF76" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the mesonotal mycangial tuft the length of the scutellum; elytral disc flat; declivital interstriae clearly punctate; declivity gradual and convex, posterolateral margins rounded; pronotum rounded when viewed dorsally (type 1); and pronotum armed by four uniformly sized coarse serrations on anterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
